    <p class="govuk-body" id="coordinateHelp">
        <strong>Coordinate Help</strong><br />
        The coordinate Viewer shows the current coordinates in the selected formats.
        <ol>
            <li>
                OS Grid
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        The Ordnance Survey National Grid reference system used in Great Britain.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Example: SU 12345 67890.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                BASEMAP
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Refers to the base map's internal coordinate system.
                    </li>
                    <li>Typically used for internal calculations or rendering.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                DD
                <ul>
                    <li>A geographic coordinate format that represents latitude and longitude as decimal fractions.</li>
                    <li>Example: 51.5074, -0.1278.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                DDM
                <ul>
                    <li>A coordinate format that combines degrees and decimal minutes.</li>
                    <li>Example: 51°30.444'N, 0°7.668'W.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                DMS
                <ul>
                    <li>A traditional coordinate format that represents latitude and longitude in degrees, minutes, and seconds.</li>
                    <li>Example: 51°30'26.64"N, 0°7'40.08"W.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                XY
                <ul>
                    <li>A Cartesian coordinate system used in map projections, typically representing easting (X) and northing (Y).</li>
                    <li>Example: X: 400000, Y: 500000.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                MGRS
                <ul>
                    <li>A coordinate system similar to MGRS, used primarily in the United States for emergency response and mapping.</li>
                    <li>Example: 30U WB 12345 67890.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                USNG
                <ul>
                    <li>A coordinate system similar to MGRS, used primarily in the United States for emergency response and mapping.</li>
                    <li>18SUJ1234567890.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                UTM
                <ul>
                    <li>A global coordinate system that divides the Earth into zones, each with its own Cartesian grid.</li>
                    <li>Example: Zone 30U, Easting: 500000, Northing: 4649776.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
